
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Conventional Commit — <type>(<scope>): <description>   (<= ~72 chars, imperative)
#
#   TYPE      fix | feat | refactor | docs | test | chore | perf | ci | build | style | revert
#   SCOPE     cli gateway tools skills agent install web cron secrets whatsapp
#             security  (or nested, e.g. apps/mobile, error-classifier, tui_gateway)
#   BREAKING  add "!" after type/scope  ->  feat(api)!: ...   (+ BREAKING CHANGE: footer)
#
# Type cheatsheet:
#   feat      new capability            fix       something was broken, now fixed
#   refactor  restructure, NO behavior  perf      makes it faster
#   docs      docs only                 test      tests only
#   chore     deps/tooling/maintenance  ci/build  pipeline / build system
#
# Body (optional) — leave a blank line, then wrap at 72 cols. Explain WHAT & WHY,
# not how. Bullet multiple changes. Link issues:  Closes #NNN / Refs #NNN
#
# DISCIPLINE (see CONTRIBUTING.md):
#   * One logical change per commit. Don't mix fix + refactor + feat.
#   * "refactor" ONLY when behavior is unchanged — else it's feat/fix.
#   * Description is specific: "drop interrupt sentinel before delivery",
#     not "fix bug".
#
# BEFORE YOU PUSH / PR:
#   * Branch name mirrors type:  feat/desc  fix/desc  docs/desc  refactor/desc
#   * Keep history connected to main (History Check rejects orphan branches —
#     never `git checkout --orphan` / re-init .git; rebase onto upstream/main).
#   * Upstreaming to Nous? Your commit email must be in scripts/release.py
#     AUTHOR_MAP, or use a GitHub +...@users.noreply.github.com address.
#   * Push target: `origin` = your fork, `upstream` = NousResearch (pull-only).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
